<HEAD>Networks Covering Gorbachev's Visit Live</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Summit Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ABC, NBC, CBS and CNN scheduled live television
coverage of Mikhail Gorbachev's activities in New York today.
   With Gorbachev speaking to the United Nations General Assembly at
11 a.m., the networks planned to carry the hour-long speech live.
   They were continuing their live coverage with arrivals and
departures from the Soviet leader's luncheon meeting with President
Reagan and President-Elect Bush.
   The networks said they will coverage Thursday's events on an
as-needed basis.
   Gorbachev's departure at 10 a.m. Friday also will be carried live.
