<DOCNO> AP881207-0026 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-07-88 0427EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w PM-BushAppointments     12-07 0108</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Bush Appointments,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>List Of Key Bush Appointees</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Bush Transition Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of Cabinet-level and other key
appointments made so far by President-elect George Bush.
   
   James A. Baker III, secretary of state.
   Nicholas Brady, treasury secretary.
   Dick Thornburgh, attorney general.
   Lauro Cavazos, education secretary.
   Robert Mosbacher, commerce secretary.
   William Webster, CIA director.
   Carla Hills, U.S. trade representative.
   Michael Boskin, chairman of the Council of Economic Advisers.
   Thomas R. Pickering, ambassador to the United Nations.
   Richard Darman, director, Office of Management and Budget.
   Brent Scowcroft, national security adviser.
   John Sununu, White House chief of staff.
   Marlin Fitzwater, White House spokesman.
