<TEXT>
   Actress Elizabeth Taylor is ``taking it easy in
California,'' recovering from recurring back problems that kept her
from attending a tribute to an AIDS researcher, her publicist said.
   Miss Taylor, who has raised millions in the fight against the
deadly disease, missed the recent fete at Carnegie Hall for Dr.
Mathilde Krim.
   ``She's had a lot of problems with her back,'' Chen Sam, Miss
Taylor's publicist, said Tuesday. ``She's alive and well and just
