<2ND_LINE>PM-Noah Robinson,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Feds Search Business office of Jackson Half-Brother</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Federal agents seized records from the office of
Jesse Jackson's half-brother Noah Robinson in an investigation into
Robinson's ownership of fast-food restaurants, officials said.
   Robinson also is charged with murder in a 1986 slaying near in
Greenville, S.C.
   The agents Tuesday sought documents dealing with his operation of
several Wendy's restaurants, said his lawyer, Jerome Rotenberg.
   Officials are looking into allegations that cash was skimmed from
the restaurants, the Chicago Tribune reported today, quoting an
unidentified source.
   Robinson is being held without bail in Greenville on charges of
hiring El Rukn street gang members to kill Leroy ``Hambone'' Barber
in 1986. Robinson is scheduled for trial in January.
   He has said he is innocent of the charges and that they and the
investigation into his business dealings were prompted by Jackson's
political success.
   The former Democratic presidential candidate has said he has had
little contact with Robinson in recent years.
</TEXT>
