<HEAD>Drugs Found Above Ceiling Panel in Plane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A maintenance worker found 154 pounds of
cocaine stashed above a ceiling panel in the rest room of an empty
Pan Am plane, an airline spokeswoman said.
   The drugs were discovered Tuesday evening, about 45 minutes after
the plane arrived at San Francisco International Airport from Miami
via Los Angeles, said spokeswoman Susan Timper.
   The airline gave no estimate of the value of the cocaine, but
such a quantity would normally be worth millions of dollars.
   The Drug Enforcement Administration searched the plane and found
no additional cocaine, Timper said. The plane was later released to
the airline and returned to service this morning.
   A secretary at DEA today said the agency had no immediate comment.
   Ms. Timper said the ceiling panel is routinely removed for
service between flights.
  
