<HEAD>Floods Displace 5,000 People In Uganda</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two weeks of torrential rains, floods and
mudslides in western Uganda have left about 5,000 people homeless, a
government official said Wednesday.
   Tents and shelter material are urgently needed for the displaced
families, said Nathan Masaba, secretary of the Ministry of Social
Relief and Rehabilitation.
   The government has delivered tents, 500 blankets, 1,000 bags of
corn flour and 100 bags of beans to victims in the mountainous
Bundibugyo district, about 200 miles west of Kampala, Masaba said.
