<1ST_LINE>u a PM-ShelterShooting 2ndLd-Writethru a0619 12-07 0211</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Shelter Shooting, 2nd Ld - Writethru, a0619,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Slain, Four Wounded At Women's Shelter</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with woman surrendering. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A resident of a battered-women's shelter shot and
killed a woman and wounded four other people this morning, then
barricaded herself briefly in her room with two children before
giving up, police said.
   The assailant had threatened to kill the children and a officer
if he entered the room, said police spokeswoman Ann Montoya.
   The motive for the shootings at the Brandon Center was not
immediately known, nor was the relationship between the woman and
the children.
   The woman, known to police only as Juanita, was thought to have a
.45-caliber semiautomatic pistol, Montoya said. Police began
negotiating with her about 9:30 a.m., a half-hour after the
shootings, said police spokesman John Wyckoff.
   A woman died at St. Anthony Hospital of a gunshot wound, Montoya
said. Two other victims were in serious condition at Denver General
Hospital, and two others were being treated there, said Montoya.
Their condition was not known.
   Police evacuated the three-story brick building of the 70 to 75
women and children living there and closed in on the woman's
basement apartment, negotiating from an apartment two doors away,
Wyckoff said.
</TEXT>
