<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Hashish     12-07 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Hashish,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seize 2 Tons of Hashish, Arrest 10</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police seized about two tons of hashish and
arrested 10 people in separate operations along the southeast coast,
authorities said.
   Three Spaniards were arrested Wednesday after police saw several
people on a beach in the southeast province of Almeria handling a
bundle containing 2,200 pounds of hashish, said Sgt. Guillermo
Visiedo of the paramilitary Civil Guard.
   Frogmen recovered about 1,320 pounds of hashish from the sea near
Murcia, about 200 miles southeast of Madrid, after a Civil Guard
patrol intercepted a boat carrying two Frenchmen and a Dutchman on
Nov. 25, said municipal spokesman Felix Alcaraz. Police arrested the
three, who were believed to have thrown the hashish overboard.
   On Tuesday, police arrested four Moroccans and seized about 500
pounds of hashish in two separate operations in the southern
province of Cadiz, officials said.
</TEXT>
