<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Labor     12-07 0097</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Labor,0099</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Labor Experts Condemn Apartheid, Call for Sanctions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Labor experts who ended a conference
Wednesday condemned South Africa's policy of apartheid and called
for mandatory economic sanctions against the government.
   ``The message is loud and clear. Africa and the rest of humanity
are one in their commitment to the elimination of apartheid from the
face of the world,'' John Nkomo, Zimbabwe's minister of labor, told
the 600 delegates at the 10-day International Labor Organization's
seventh annual African Conference.
   The conference also focused on the need to train more women for
work.
</TEXT>
