<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Reconstruction     12-07 0121</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Iran-Reconstruction,0125</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iran Allocates $500 Million For Reconstruction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran's Parliament on Wednesday approved
more than $500 million for rebuilding housing, businesses and
facilities devastated by the eight-year Persian Gulf war, Tehran
radio reported.
   About $150 million of the sum will be used for educational,
medical and agricultural projects, according to the report,
monitored in Nicosia.
   Western analysts estimate Iran will need up to $400 billion in
the next decade to reconstruct its war-torn economy.
   West Germany signed an agreement in Tehran on Tuesday to finance
and provide technical assistance in manufacturing construction
materials in Iran.
   Iranian Minister of Housing and Urban Development Serajeddin
Kazerooni said similar agreements are being negotiated with the
Soviet Union and Poland.
</TEXT>
