<HEAD>Company Sold Six Times Too Many Winning Lottery Tickets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The organizers of a lottery may have
to give away 36 cars instead of the planned six because too many
winning tickets were printed, the sponsor said.
   Philip Chaubert, spokesman for the Distributa company, said each
person with the winning number, 22, who claims the prize will be
awarded a car worth about $10,000.
   ``We will honor the winners,'' he said.
   The deadline for claiming the prizes is next week, Chaubert said.
   The mountain village of Prassurgny, with less than 100
inhabitants, already has three winners, he said.
   The company sponsored the event for two store chains that control
2,500 retail outlets in Switzerland.
