   The man chosen by President-elect George Bush
to be his chief economic adviser has advocated major changes in
Social Security and other entitlement programs, calling for a
``major attack'' on benefits to the middle class.
   In a book last year assessing the Reagan administration's
economic track record, Michael Boskin wrote that President Reagan's
