Airlines for alleged health violations involving cadmium dust
exposure.
   OSHA inspectors found the alleged violations after an inspection
at the landing gear shop located at Miami International Airport. The
inspection began June 7, and the fines were proposed Tuesday.
   Eastern officials will meet with OSHA Dec. 21 to discuss the
proposed fine, company spokeswoman Karen Ceremsak said.
