   A regulation to require anti-fume devices on
gas tanks of new vehicles is unlikely to be issued before the Bush
administration takes office, the Environmental Protection Agency
says.
   ``Our legal requirements are we have a public hearing, give two
weeks notice minimum, and the record be open for 30 days after the
hearing,'' said Dick Wilson, director of the EPA's office of mobile
sources. ``I think it is pretty hard to squeeze that in in the time
remaining.''
