<2ND_LINE>BC-Taiwan-Trade,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Taiwan's Trade Surplus Narrows In November</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Taiwan's trade surplus shrank slightly in
November, the government reported Wednesday.
   Last months' surplus fell to $1.15 billion from $1.21 billion in
October and $1.51 billion in November 1987, according to the
ccounting and Statistics.
   Exports in November totaled $5.45 billion, up 0.9 percent over
the previous month and up 5.1 percent from last year. Imports
reached $4.31 billion, up from $4.19 billion in October and $3.67
billion last year.
   For the first 11 months, Taiwan registered a total surplus of
$9.76 billion, down 45.17 percent from the same period last year.
