<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Saatchi     12-07 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Saatchi,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Advertising Group Posts 7.9 Percent Profit Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Saatchi & Saatchi Co. PLC, one of the world's
biggest advertising and communications groups, reported Wednesday
that its after-tax profit rose 7.9 percent in its latest fiscal year.
   After-tax profit in the year ended Sept. 30 came to 75.1 million
pounds, or about $133 million, from 69.6 million pounds a year
earlier.
   Pre-tax profit grew 11 percent to 138 million pounds, or about
$244 million, from 124.1 million pounds a year earlier.
   Sales rose 11 percent to 862.2 million pounds, or about $1.53
billion, from 773.8 million pounds a year earlier.
   It said its communications activities, which includes its
advertising business, produced 78 percent of its latest year's
sales, or about 673.8 million pounds compared with 642 million
pounds a year earlier. Its agencies include Saatchi & Saatchi
Advertising Worldwide, Backer Spielvogel Bates and
Campbell-Mithun-Esty Advertising.
   Consulting revenue grew to 188.4 million pounds from 131.8
million pounds a year earlier.
   Saatchi didn't break out quarterly or half-year results. It isn't
required to under British law.
</TEXT>
